  "body": "* Bug Report\r\n\r\nDeviation from expected behavior:  No Minio pods are created after deploying object-store.yaml\r\n\r\nrook-minio-operator logs shows:\r\n\r\n> minio-op-object: failed to validate object store config\r\n\r\nExpected behavior: Minio pods would be turned up\r\n\r\nHow to reproduce it (minimal and precise):  Used example yaml files from v1 release per the Quickstart.  Only changes made to the yaml files were:\r\n\r\nobject store yaml:  access keys, changed nodeCount to 3, and set storage resource to 50Gi\r\noperator yaml:  Per Rancher OS and pod inspection, this path is bound inside the containers.\r\n\r\n> env:\r\n>         - name: FLEXVOLUME_DIR_PATH\r\n>           value: \"/var/lib/kubelet/volumeplugins\"\r\n\r\n\r\n* OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):  ROS 1.5.1\r\n* Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):  4.14.85-rancher #1 SMP Sat Dec 1 12:40:08 UTC 2018 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n* Rook version (use `rook version` inside of a Rook Pod): 1.0.0\r\n* Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):  1.13.4\r\n* Kubernetes cluster type (e.g. Tectonic, GKE, OpenShift):  RKE on VMWare\r\n\r\n\r\n",
